1 Demographic Characteristics

1.1 Sample characteristics

ℹ️ Total sample size is 2,002 and includes a roughly equal number of female and male participants. The majority of participants are aged between 15-19 years. A larger proportion of participants reside in rural areas compared to urban areas. Most participants have completed primary education, with a significant number also having completed secondary education. Only a small proportion have an education level of secondary and above.

Characteristic Overall, N = 2,0021 Gender

1.2 Relationship status

ℹ️ Majority of young people are either single or dating (93%).

1.3 Own children

ℹ️ Majority of the respondents do not have children of their own.

1.4 Biggest change in your life in the past 12 months

ℹ️ Overall, majority of the respondents experienced a negative change in the past 12 months.

1.5 Concerning issues

2.2 Mobile phone ownership

ℹ️ 71% of the youth own a mobile phone. Of those that own a mobile phone, 80% have at least one smartphone.

  • Basic phone – only allows calling, messaging, saving numbers
  • Feature phone – has camera, radio, basic internet
  • Smartphone – has a touch screen, mobile applications, e.g., WhatsApp, Instagram, TikTok

2.3 Times Youth Go Online

ℹ️ The most common times youth go online is 6pm - 10pm and 10pm - 2pm

2.4 Favourite Activities

ℹ️ The most common first choice activities youth do online include looking for entertainment, check what is new with friends, and posting personal pictures.

2.5 Platform visit frequency

ℹ️ Majority of youth visit WhatsApp, Facebook, Instagram and Tiktok at least once a day.

2.6 Platform Ranking

ℹ️ WhatsApp, Facebook, Instagram and Tiktok are the first choice most important platforms.

2.7 Media perception

ℹ️ In general, young people think that media content is relatable, understandable, and inspiring

3 Shujaaz awareness

3.1 Character Awareness

ℹ️ Character awareness varies significantly.

3.2 Awareness of Shujaaz Cartoon booklet

ℹ️ Approximately 68% of young people are aware of Shujaaz cartoon booklet.

3.3 Awareness of various programs

ℹ️ Awareness of Shujaaz’s programs is low and varies significantly from program to program.

3.4 Overall reach

ℹ️ 8,014,277 (70%) young people are aware of Shujaaz media. These results include prompted and un-prompted reach.

3.5 Reach by persona

ℹ️ Brand awareness across all personas is largely similar (no significant differences).

3.6 Reach by location

ℹ️ Brand awareness significantly varies by location.

4.4 Cartoon booklet sources

ℹ️ Majority of youth who use the cartoon booklet, get it from friends, kiosks, newspapers and school library. Other sources commonly mentioned include barbershops and Cyber cafe.

4.9 Perception of Shujaaz characters

ℹ️ Overall, Shujaaz is perceived positively in terms of humor, inspiration, relatability, and trust. However, there is a significant perception that it caters more to a younger audience and some difficulty with understanding the language used by the characters.

Indicator Strongly disagree Disagree Neutral Agree Strongly agree
People and characters in Shujaaz are funny 1% 3% 2% 25% 69%
People and characters in Shujaaz are inspiring 4% 5% 2% 28% 61%
People/characters in Shujaaz resemble people I know – my friends, classmates, etc 10% 9% 3% 35% 43%
Shujaaz is entertainments for small kids, not adults like me and my friends 52% 19% 3% 13% 12%
I respect Shujaaz people/characters and trust them 5% 9% 2% 33% 50%
I can freely talk to Shujaaz people/characters and share my thoughts, ideas, concerns and fears 11% 11% 3% 32% 43%
I like Shujaaz, it’s fun 2% 4% 2% 19% 73%
Shujaaz speaks the same language as an ordinary young Kenyan 4% 7% 2% 29% 58%
I have difficulty understanding Sheng in Shujaaz, nobody in my areas speaks like Shujaaz characters 46% 20% 3% 18% 13%
Information from Shujaaz does not need double-checking, if it’s in Shujaaz it is true 17% 22% 3% 32% 25%
When other people question my decisions, I tell them I learned it from Shujaaz 26% 19% 3% 30% 22%
Shujaaz shows life situations that are familiar to me 6% 9% 2% 33% 50%

4.10 Shujaaz Recommendation

ℹ️ For engaged users, 52% (3,645,870) have ever recommended Shujaaz to other people.
